WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:01.334
In Return of the Ancients, 

00:00:01.334 --> 00:00:05.672
we're adding a set of Challenges
for the first time to a Path of Exile 2 league.

00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:07.574
Every two challenges you complete

00:00:07.574 --> 00:00:10.193
will give you a piece of the 
Knight of Aldur Armour set,

00:00:10.193 --> 00:00:11.795
so it’s worth giving them a shot.

00:00:12.362 --> 00:00:15.148
To check out your progression and 
requirements to complete a challenge,

00:00:15.148 --> 00:00:17.801
 just hit ‘H’ to open up the Challenges screen.

00:00:17.951 --> 00:00:19.319
There are eight challenges in all,

00:00:19.319 --> 00:00:22.222
and they progress from pretty easy, 
to pretty hard.

00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:23.923
To complete The Runeseeker,

00:00:23.923 --> 00:00:26.626
you'll need to find remnants with 
an ever growing number of slots 

00:00:26.626 --> 00:00:28.595
and use them to craft new items.

00:00:29.229 --> 00:00:32.999
The seven slot crafts can be 
pretty challenging with six waves of enemies,

00:00:32.999 --> 00:00:36.002
so attempting one of these fights
could require some skill.

00:00:38.638 --> 00:00:39.639
Throughout the campaign,

00:00:39.639 --> 00:00:41.408
there are many optional bosses.

00:00:41.408 --> 00:00:42.959
To complete the Hunter,

00:00:42.959 --> 00:00:45.361
you will need to hunt down six of them. 

00:00:45.361 --> 00:00:49.282
The last two, Akthi, the Final Sting 
and Anundr, the Sandworm

00:00:49.282 --> 00:00:51.551
can be pretty tough to find being 
in the Khari Crossing.

00:00:52.185 --> 00:00:55.271
In order to track them down, 
follow the dry river bed.

00:00:55.388 --> 00:00:57.073
You'll find their arena at the end.

00:00:58.558 --> 00:01:00.877
The Ascendant requires you to gain
all eight points

00:01:00.877 --> 00:01:03.880
of your ascendancy class
by doing ascendancy trials.

00:01:03.880 --> 00:01:06.766
Getting the final set of points
can be pretty challenging though.

00:01:06.766 --> 00:01:10.220
You will either need to defeat Zarokh on the 4th level of the Trial of the Sekhemas,

00:01:10.653 --> 00:01:14.390
or defeat the Trialmaster from the Trial of Chaos by finding all three keys.

00:01:15.141 --> 00:01:16.960
Of the two, the Trial of Chaos

00:01:16.960 --> 00:01:20.029
will take you much longer due to having to run the trial multiple times, 

00:01:20.029 --> 00:01:22.549
but the Trial of the Sekhemas 
is more challenging,

00:01:22.549 --> 00:01:25.151
so you will have to decide which of 
these two paths to take.

00:01:26.719 --> 00:01:28.138
The Reliquarian is simple.

00:01:28.138 --> 00:01:30.573
Identify 50 different unique items. 

00:01:32.025 --> 00:01:33.910
Having a tough time finding uniques?

00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:37.647
Jado, The Atlas Master has a lot of abilities
that specialise in finding them.

00:01:39.749 --> 00:01:41.151
To complete The Artisan

00:01:41.151 --> 00:01:43.720
you will need to use a bunch of different crafting items.

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.839
All of which come from Remnant encounters.

00:01:47.240 --> 00:01:48.441
For the Cartographer,

00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:50.894
you'll need to allocate your entire Atlas Tree.

00:01:51.177 --> 00:01:52.712
All 300 nodes.

00:01:53.163 --> 00:01:56.883
You can do this the slow way by completing
all the maps inside the fortress.

00:01:56.916 --> 00:01:58.918
But there is another way too. 

00:01:58.918 --> 00:02:01.054
Each time you defeat the Arbiter of Divinity, 

00:02:01.054 --> 00:02:05.175
you will gain the ability to automatically complete a large section of the fortress. 

00:02:06.676 --> 00:02:09.679
Find keys to his fight
by searching for Citadels in the Atlas.

00:02:09.829 --> 00:02:12.832
Each of them have big glowing beams
so you can see them in the fog.

00:02:13.032 --> 00:02:16.719
After fighting him four times,
the entire fortress will be completed.

00:02:17.871 --> 00:02:21.040
And last,
but certainly not least, The Vanquisher.

00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:24.010
This challenge requires killing 
three Pinnacle bosses,

00:02:24.010 --> 00:02:25.478
the hardest fights in the game.

00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:27.030
Tangmazu,

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:28.097
the Bodach,

00:02:28.097 --> 00:02:29.682
and the Vessel of Kulemak.

00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:34.070
These are the pinnacles of Delirium,
Ritual, and Abyss leagues,

00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:37.190
so you will need to do these three quest lines in order to do this challenge.

00:02:37.674 --> 00:02:39.909
One important thing with 
the Vessel of Kulemak though,

00:02:39.909 --> 00:02:42.162
is you need to defeat him at full strength.

00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:44.113
That means risking
the item during the boss fight

00:02:44.113 --> 00:02:46.716
by returning the finger, 
and defeating him anyway.

00:02:49.352 --> 00:02:50.303
As I said before,

00:02:50.303 --> 00:02:53.223
every two challenges you complete will get you pieces of the armour set,

00:02:53.223 --> 00:02:55.675
so you don't have to do
all of them to get some rewards.

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:58.628
But if you do, you'll be able
to show off your prowess,

00:02:58.778 --> 00:03:02.715
because everyone in global chat, or in the forums can see how many challenges you’ve earned.

00:03:03.149 --> 00:03:05.835
You'll also get this Totem Decoration
for your hideout,

00:03:05.835 --> 00:03:07.837
meaning that forever
more people who trade with you

00:03:07.837 --> 00:03:10.840
will be able to see that you were there,
and you defeated the league.

00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:15.361
Try out these challenges and more on May 29th, 
in the Return of the Ancients.

00:03:15.562 --> 00:03:17.463
Thanks for watching and see you then!

